Boot floppy for Oralux installed on hard disk

* Copy menu.lst to /tmp

* Update it: by default Oralux is supposed to be installed in hda5.
Search lines at the end of menu.lst:
title		Oralux 0.7 alpha
root		(hd0,4)

and change (hd0,4) accordingly.
 
* Insert a floppy (Warning: all its data will be lost: the floppy will be formatted).

* Run:
./bootHDinstall

* Reboot your PC